history.content: 126 is mostly a combination of Stat 134 and Stat 150, with some additional topics at the end like multivariate Gaussians and Kalman filters. I don't think it would cover enough new content, but I'm also not a Stats major.

children.subject: Assuming you're CS/EECS and not majoring in anything else, there's not a problem in terms of getting credit. In terms of whether you should take it, after Stat 134/135/150, it would be better to self learn the remaining material, but that's just me

history.content: Hi! I am wondering if there is any restriction on the upper-division major requirement that EE126 cannot be used as a 4-units technical course after taking some stats upper-div courses (such as 134, 135, 150) (in other words, can I still get credit)? Since I planned to take COMPSCI 189 in the future and I was told that EE126 may be an important course, and I check the course website and found that the content of 126 is still different from those course, so I am wonder if 126 could still satisfy the major requirement after some stats courses? Thanks!
